The '''Sajjada Nashin''' (hereditary administrator) also refers as '''Trusty''' (a successor) is the descendant of a [[Sufi]] or [[Pir (Sufism)|Pir]] and in some instances descendant of a disciple of a Sufi, A Sajjada particularly tends to the [[shrine]] which is made over the Sufi's [[tomb]] or [[Grave (burial)|grave]], known as a [[Dargah]] or [[Mazar (mausoleum)|Mazar]]. A trusty is a key person who held and leads the traditional Sufi rituals in Dargah's daily activities and particularly during ''[[Urs]]''—(death anniversary).

